//////// Disable PC-Spekaer terminal

  echo "blacklist pcspkr" | sudo tee /etc/modprobe.d/nobeep.conf ---> and reboot.
It creates a file nobeep.conf to /etc/modprobe.d/ that contains the line blacklist pcspkr, and disables the pc speaker.
https://www.reddit.com/r/Fedora/comments/i4jci9/disable_hardware_beep/
https://www.reddit.com/r/linuxquestions/comments/ve9j5r/my_desktop_started_beeping_on_power_off_why/


